<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870206-0032 </DOCNO><HL> Masco Industries Inc.Is Selling 10 1/4% NotesTotaling $250 Million</HL><DD> 02/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MASXBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Masco Industries Inc. is offering $250 million of 10 1/4% senior subordinated notes.    The notes were priced at 99.5 to yield 10.33%, and they mature in 1997. The size of the offering was increased from an originally planned $160 million.    Proceeds will be used to reduce bank debt.    Taylor, Mich.-based Masco makes custom-engineered components and other specialty commercial and industry products. Smith Barney, Harris Upham andamp; Co. is the head underwriter. </TEXT></DOC>